<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-03-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-03-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="387" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/98: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-02T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 2,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>83. Department’s 78, February 25, 7 p.m.<note n="27" xml:id="d387fn27">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <p>Inform Chinese Foreign Office that Federal Telegraph Company ratified
                            contract March 1st.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
